C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20is%20comfortably%20in%20soft%20landing%20territory%2C%20but%20Paul%20Krugman%20says%20it%20isn't%20altogether%20clear%20that%20it%20will%20stay%20that%20way.%20In%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F12%2Fopinion%2Finflation-soft-landing-economy-unemployment.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%20for%20the%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20famed%20Nobel%20laureate%20highlighted%20an%20unexpected%20uptick%20in%20unemployment%20as%20reason%20for%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20focused%20on%20a%20recession%20indicator%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FSAHMCURRENT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESahm%20Rule%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20says%20that%20when%20the%20unemployment%20rate's%20three-month%20moving%20average%20climbs%2050%20basis%20points%20from%20a%2012-month%20low%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20in%20the%20first%20stages%20of%20a%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20still%20below%20that%20critical%200.5%20level%2C%20but%20I%20am%20worried%20that%20high%20interest%20rates%20may%20finally%20be%20taking%20their%20toll%20and%20that%20by%20keeping%20rates%20high%2C%20the%20Fed%20is%20running%20the%20risk%20of%20finally%20making%20all%20those%20wrong%20recession%20calls%20come%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20wrote%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-unemployment-work-labor-market-wage-growth-in-february-2024-3%5C%22%3EFebruary's%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20triggered%20these%20concerns%2C%20as%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20unexpectedly%20rose%20to%203.9%25%20from%203.7%25.%20This%20hotter-than-expected%20reading%20stressed%20other%20analysts%20as%20well%2C%20who%20voiced%20worries%20of%20a%20surprise%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20that%20the%20jobless%20rate%20is%20up%200.5%20of%20a%20percentage%20point%20from%20the%20January%202023%20cycle%20low%2C%20it%20messes%20up%20the%20soft%20landing%20narrative%20because%20once%20it%20rises%20this%20much%20from%20the%20lows%2C%20the%20recession%20nobody%20ever%20sees%20coming%20arrives%2C%26quot%3B%20economist%20David%20Rosenberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-recession-economy-outlook-unemployment-rate-rise-february-jobs-report-2024-3%5C%22%3Ewrote%20last%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrugman%20notes%20that%20on%20other%20fronts%2C%20however%2C%20soft%20landing%20advocates%20have%20a%20stronger%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20consumer%20price%20index%20inflation%20data%20has%20outpaced%20expectations%20two%20months%20in%20a%20row%20now%2C%20these%20recent%20reports%20are%20not%20completely%20in%20line%20with%20reality%2C%20Krugman%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20where%20core%20inflation%20rose%203.8%25%20on%20an%20annual%20basis%2C%20this%20measure%20is%20more%20of%20a%20snapshot%20of%20the%20past%2C%20he%20said.%20That's%20as%20it's%20largely%20driven%20by%20shelter%20prices%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20lag%20in%20official%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20when%20volatile%20items%20such%20as%20food%2C%20energy%2C%20used%20cars%2C%20and%20shelter%20are%20excluded%2C%20the%20six-month%20change%20in%20consumer%20prices%20has%20risen%20at%20a%20more%20modest%202.8%25%20annual%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEventually%20something%20will%20go%20wrong%2C%20because%20something%20always%20does%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20forecast.%20%26quot%3BBut%20compared%20with%20the%20dire%20predictions%20of%20many%20economists%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20political%20critics%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%20we're%20still%20in%20incredibly%20good%20shape.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-recession-outlook-rising-unemployment-biggest-threat-sahm-rule-krugman-2024-3%5C