20homes%2C%20valued%20at%20a%20combined%20%2420%20trillion%2C%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20extreme%20heat%2C%20wind%2C%20and%20poor%20air%20quality%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Realtor.com%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20tools%20come%20as%20climate-fueled%20disasters%20intensify%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwildfires-drought-climate-change-fleeing-expensive-cities-to-dangerous-places-2023-8%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRising%2520housing%2520costs%2520have%2520helped%2Cdisproportionately%2520on%2520less%2520affluent%2520people.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20people%20move%20into%20disaster-prone%20parts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20country%20including%20Florida%2C%20California%2C%20and%20Texas.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeowners%20in%20Miami%20hold%20the%20highest%20value%20of%20homes%20at%20risk%20for%20severe%20or%20extreme%20heat%20(%241.26%20trillion)%2C%20while%20San%20Francisco%20homeowners%20hold%20the%20highest%20value%20of%20homes%20at%20risk%20for%20severe%20air%20quality%20(%241.28%20trillion)%2C%20according%20to%20Realtor.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trends%20are%20scrambling%20insurance%20companies%2C%20which%20one%20executive%20told%20Business%20Insider%20can%20no%20longer%20rely%20on%20the%20old%20models%20they%20once%20used%20to%20predict%20the%20chances%20and%20severity%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20has%20been%20a%20surprise.%20They're%20in%20panic%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20insurance%20executive%20Oscar%20Seikaly%20said%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20insurance%20companies%20have%20pulled%20out%20of%20California%20and%20Florida%20over%20concerns%20about%20increasingly%20volatile%20wildfires%20and%20hurricanes%2C%20respectively.%20In%20some%20California%20towns%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-insurers-will-shape-where-people-live-climate-change-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomeowners%20can%20no%20longer%20find%20property%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20Florida%20condo%20market%20has%20ground%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-condo-owners-prices-drop-insurance-hoa-taxes-increase-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20a%20halt%20over%20rising%20insurance%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20homeowners%20have%20given%20up%20searching%20for%20insurance%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20being%20on%20the%20Titanic%2C%26quot%3B%20Bob%20Stephens%2C%20who%20couldn't%20find%20insurance%20for%20his%20%243%20million%20Florida%20home%2C%20said%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%20you're%20going%20down.%20How%20are%20you%20going%20to%20stop%20it%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUnderstanding%20your%20home's%20climate%20risk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20releasing%20the%20heat%2C%20wind%2C%20and%20air%20quality%20tools%2C%20Realtor.com%20already%20provided%20fire%20and%20flood%20risks%20for%20properties%20based%20on%20data%20from%20First%20Street.%20First%20Street%2C%20a%20climate-risk%20firm%2C%20is%20also%20behind%20the%20data%20on%20extreme%20heat%2C%20wind%2C%20and%20air%20quality%20now%20added%20to%20listings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffirststreet.org%2Fpress%2Ffirst-street-releases-10th-national-risk-assessment-atrocious-air%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eair-quality%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20includes%20two%20common%20pollutants%3A%20particulate%20matter%2C%20often%20caused%20by%20wildfire%20smoke%2C%20and%20ozone%2C%20which%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Fozone-pollution-and-your-patients-health%2Fwhat-ozone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20is%20the%20result%20of%20reactions%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20other%20pollutants%20from%20chemical%20plants%2C%20tailpipes%2C%20and%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20risk%20scores%20will%20help%20homebuyers%20make%20an%20informed%20decision%20about%20whether%20to%20go%20through%20with%20a%20purchase%2C%20Realtor.com%20Chief%20Economist%20Danielle%20Hale%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHale%20added%20that%20the%20company%20has%20studied%20whether%20property-level%20climate%20risk%20data%20shifts%20homebuying%20decisions.%20The%20answer%20is%20complicated%20because%20people%20consider%20many%20different%20factors%20before%20buying%20a%20home.%20How%20recently%20a%20flood%20or%20fire%20happened%20in%20the%20area%20tends%20to%20have%20an%20impact.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20affordability%20often%20trumps%20climate-risk%20calculations%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20often%20the%20case%20that%20homes%20in%20areas%20with%20the%20greatest%20risk%20of%20fire%20also%20tend%20to%20be%20the%20cheapest%20on%20a%20per-square-foot%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20Hale%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20parts%20of%20California%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-hotter-drier-lightning-fires-bigger-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhere%20catastrophic%20wildfires%20are%20increasing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurveys%20show%20that%20affordability%20remains%20the%20top%20priority%20even%20as%20homebuyers%20increasingly%20consider%20climate%20and%20environmental%20hazards.%20Zillow%20found%20that%2036%25%20of%20millennials%20and%2019%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20homebuyers%20they%20surveyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-buying-homes-stress-about-climate-risk-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20considering%20moving%20to%20areas%20with%20climate%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finvestors.redfin.com%2Fnews-events%2Fpress-releases%2Fdetail%2F1047%2Fredfin-reports-people-are-moving-out-of-areas-with-poor-air%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20by%20Redfin%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20about%201.2%20million%20more%20homeowners%20and%20renters%20moved%20out%20of%20than%20into%20cities%20with%20high%20risk%20of%20poor%20air%20quality%20between%20202