re%20for%20either%20higher%20taxes%20or%20higher%20inflation%2C%20and%20in%20either%20scenario%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20own%20stocks%20as%20the%20most%20tax-efficient%20strategy%2C%20according%20to%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20ways%20to%20boost%20the%20tax%20efficiency%20of%20investment%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E1.%20Own%20ETFs%20over%20mutual%20funds%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BETFs%20are%20more%20tax%20efficient%20than%20mutual%20funds%20thanks%20to%20the%20creation%20and%20redemption%20process%20for%20shares%2C%26quot%3B%20Bank%20of%20America%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMutual%20funds%20are%20sometimes%20forced%20to%20sell%20assets%20to%20meet%20redemption%20requests.%20Any%20realized%20capital%20gains%20from%20sales%20are%20distributed%20to%20shareholders%2C%20triggering%20a%20tax%20event.%20On%20average%2C%20mutual%20fund%20tax%20events%20cost%20investors%201.3%25%20per%20year%20vs%20just%200.4%25%20for%20ETFs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E2.%20Stocks%20are%20more%20tax-efficient%20than%20bonds%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20income%20paid%20by%20US%20government%20bonds%20is%20taxable%20at%20federal%20ordinary%20income%20rates%2C%20up%20to%2037%25%20for%20top%20earners.%20Interest%20from%20cash%20accounts%2C%20I-bonds%2C%20and%20other%20fixed%20income%20is%20also%20taxable%20as%20ordinary%20income.%20Most%20equity%20payouts%2C%20however%2C%20are%20classified%20as%20qualified%20dividend%20income%2C%20and%20taxed%20at%20a%20maximum%20rate%20of%2020%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Bank%20of%20America%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3E3.%20When%20owning%20bonds%2C%20focus%20on%20municipals%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20investors'%20bond%20allocations%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20focus%20on%20high-yielding%20issues%20in%20the%20municipal%20space%2C%20as%20well%20as%20preferred%20ETFs%2C%20which%20act%20as%20quasi-bond%20funds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20two%20types%20of%20fixed-income%20investments%20not%20only%20get%20taxed%20at%20lower%20rates%20than