limate-action-30-global-leaders-climate-solutions-2023-11%23pablo-ribeiro-dias-cofounder-and-cto-solarcycle-19%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20reclaims%20old%20solar%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20new%20ones%2C%20in%20February%20announced%20plans%20for%20a%20glass%20factory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223590%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22SK%20On%20and%20Hyundai's%20battery%20factory%20under%20construction%20in%20Cartersville%2C%20Georgia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f0913d90413ab8e1dbd780%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221660%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESK%20On%20and%20Hyundai%20are%20building%20an%20electric%20vehicle%20battery%20factory%20in%20Cartersville%2C%20Georgia.%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Boudreau%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPat%20Wilson%2C%20the%20commissioner%20of%20the%20Georgia%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Development%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20recruiting%20solar%20and%20electric-vehicle%20companies%20was%20strategic.%20Wilson%20said%20that%20on%20a%20trip%20to%20Germany%20his%20department%20organized%20with%20Gov.%20Brian%20Kemp%20shortly%20after%20he%20took%20office%20in%202019%2C%20executives%20they%20met%20with%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fporsche-unveils-mission-x-new-electric-hypercar-ev-electric-vehicle-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPorsche%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmercedes-benz-ev-2030-electric-car-market-trends-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMercedes-Benz%3C%2Fa%3E%20talked%20at%20length%20about%20electric%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQcells%20had%20already%20selected%20Dalton%20for%20its%20new%20solar-panel%20factory%20by%20the%20time%20Kemp%20was%20elected.%20Wilson%20said%20that%20was%20partly%20because%20of%20Georgia's%20decadeslong%20business%20relationship%20with%20South%20Korea%2C%20where%20the%20state%20established%20an%20office%20in%201985.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilson%20said%20he%20met%20with%20SK%20On's%20officials%20several%20times%20before%20it%20looked%20to%20open%20a%20battery%20factory%20in%20the%20Southeast.%20SK%20On%20opened%20two%20battery%20plants%20in%20Commerce%2C%20Georgia%2C%20in%202018%20and%20hired%20some%203%2C000%20workers%2C%20though%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F9453dc6b-be15-4a54-8e26-fffdc7a3c9eb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20laid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20more%20than%20100%20employees%20as%20automakers%20slowed%20EV%20investments%2C%20the%20Financial%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20ties%20to%20South%20Korean%20conglomerates%2C%20Georgia%20invests%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20dollars%20a%20year%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20workforce%20training%2C%20budget%20documents%20show.%20A%20state-funded%20program%20known%20as%20Quick%20Start%20can%20be%20tailored%20to%20the%20technical%20skills%20companies%20are%20looking%20for%20and%20offered%20for%20free%20to%20workers.%20Georgia's%20network%20of%2022%20technical%20colleges%20also%20partners%20with%20local%20companies%20to%20prepare%20students%20for%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeidi%20Popham%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Georgia%20Northwestern%20Technical%20College%2C%20said%20the%20state%20agency%20that%20oversees%20that%20network%20of%20technical%20colleges%20developed%20an%20electric-vehicle-technician%20certificate%2C%20given%20the%20massive%20growth%20of%20that%20industry.%20She%20expects%20her%20college%20will%20offer%20that%20certification%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20students%20in%20our%20automotive-technician%20program%20that%20work%20on%20the%20vehicles%20will%20have%20to%20have%20those%20skills%2C%26quot%3B%20Popham%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20looms%20large%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgia's%20strategy%20in%20recruitment%20and%20workforce%20development%20is%20only%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20boom%20in%20renewable-energy-technology%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-solar-tariffs-solar-panels-thousands-of-job-losses-2018-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslapped%20tariffs%20on%20imports%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20solar%20panels%20and%20cells%2C%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20helping%20US%20manufacturers%20compete%20with%20cheaper%20imports%20from%20China%20and%20Southeast%20Asia.%20The%20tariffs%20were%20requested%20by%20two%20American%20companies%2C%20including%20Suniva%2C%20which%20had%20once%20been%20the%20fastest-growing%20solar%20company%20in%20the%20US%20before%20filing%20for%20bankruptcy%20protection%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForeign%20companies%20shipping%20to%20the%20US%2C%20including%20Hanwha%2C%20were%20forced%20to%20reevaluate%20their%20supply%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20factories%20in%20Korea%20and%20Malaysia%20that%20were%20impacted%20by%20that%20duty%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Scott%20Moskowitz%2C%20the%20director%20of%20strategy%20and%20market%20intelligence%20at%20Qcells.%20%26quot%3BThe%20US%20was%20our%20largest%20market%2C%20and%20we%20had%20long%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20factory%20here.%20But%20that%20trade%20policy%20jump-started%20us%20making%20the%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQcells'%20latest%20expansion%20plans%20were%20buoyed%20by%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act.%20The%20law%20authorized%20big%20tax%20credits%20for%20companies%20making%20renewable-energy%20technologies%2C%20including%20solar%20panels%2C%20batteries%2C%20and%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20subsidies%20could%20increase%20if%20companies%20use%20what's%20known%20as%20domestic%20content%3A%20components%20of%20those%20technologies%20that%20are%20also%20sourced%20from%20the%20US.%20The%20Treasury%20Department%20is%20still%20working%20on%20final%20guidance%20for%20which%20components%20would%20qualify.%20An%20initial%20draft%20covers%20solar%20modules%20and%20cells%20but%20not%20wafers%20and%20polysilicon.%20In%20February%2C%20a%20dozen%20senators%2C%20including%20Sen.%20Jon%20Ossoff%20of%20Georgia%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ossoff.senate.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F24.02.28_Sen.-Ossoff-Domestic-Content.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%20the%20Biden%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20include%20wafers%20and%20polysilicon%20to%20help%20reshore%20more%20of%20the%20solar-panel%20supply%20chain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20change%20would%20benefit%20Qcells.%20Its%20parent%20company%2C%20Hanwha%2C%20invested%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kedglobal.com%2Fenergy%2FnewsView%2Fked202311160013%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolysilicon%20factory%20in%20Washington%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reviving%20operations%20after%20a%20nearly%20five-year%20hiatus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskowitz%20said%20that%20though%20the%20law%20has%20spurred%20the%20most%20investment%20in%20US%20manufacturing%20in%20decades%2C%20these%20renewable%20supply%20chains%20still%20face%20headwinds%2C%20primarily%20from%20China.%20He%20added%20that%20China%20had%20compensated%20for%20its%20cratering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-economy-crash-real-estate-collapse-property-market-evergrande-bass-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal-estate%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20rapidly%20investing%20in%20export-oriented%20manufacturing%20inside%20and%20outside%20its%20borders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FoKc4g%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Investments%20in%20the%20energy%20transition%20in%202023%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20BloombergNEF%2C%20China%20spent%20%24676%20billion%20on%20the%20green-energy%20transition%20in%202023%2C%20while%20the%20US%20spent%20%24303%20billion.%20The%20year%20prior%2C%20China%20spent%20%24546%20billion%20while%20the%20US%20spent%20%24141%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frenewable-energy-how-much-added-wind-solar-evs-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20dominates%20the%20renewable-energy%20supply%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%20metals%20to%20polysilicon%20to%20solar%20components%20to%20batteries.%20The%20investment%20has%20also%20led%20to%20a%20global%20oversupply%20of%20solar%20panels%20and%20components%20that's%20sent%20prices%20plunging%2C%20and%20it's%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-crush-tesla-elon-musk-american-ev-industry-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBYD%2520eclipsed%2520Tesla%2520in%25202023%2Con%2520threats%2520from%2520Chinese%2520automakers.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20a%20major%20player%20in%20the%20EV%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20doesn't%20import%20solar%20panels%20directly%20from%20China%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commerce.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F08%2Fdepartment-commerce-issues-final-determination-circumvention-inquiries%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20year%20determined%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20certain%20Chinese%20companies%20were%20shipping%20products%20through%20Southeast%20Asian%20countries%20like%20Malaysia%20and%20Vietnam.%20This%20allowed%20those%20companies%20to%20avoid%20tariffs%2C%20which%20the%20administration%20had%20waived%20for%20two%20years%2C%20through%20June%202024.%20According%20to%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%2C%20the%20US%20imported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Fextreme-dependence-us-solar-panel-imports-boom-to-record-54-gw-in-2023-80448513%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20its%20solar%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Southeast%20Asia%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moves%20reflect%20the%20delicate%20balance%20the%20White%20House%20is%20trying%20to%20strike%20between%20meeting%20its%20climate%20and%20renewable-energy%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20which%20rely%20on%20imports%20%E2%80%94%20and%20bolstering%20a%20domestic%20manufacturing%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoskowitz%20said%20that%20despite%20the%20difficult%20market%20conditions%2C%20Qcells%20was%20committed%20to%20its%20US%20expansion%20plans.%20The%20tax%20breaks%20in%20the%20Inflation%20Reduction%20Act%20are%20in%20effect%20for%2010%20years%2C%20which%20he%20said%20reduced%20some%20risk%20for%20the%20company.%20Qcells%20also%20has%20an%20eight-year%20supply%20deal%20with%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20is%20building%20out%20renewable-energy%20projects%20to%20power%20its%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Qcells%20factory%20in%20Cartersville%20is%20finished%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it%20will%20produce%20about%208.4%20gigawatts%20of%20solar%20power%20capacity%20a%20year%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seia.org%2Fus-solar-market-insight%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20a%20fourth%20of%20what%20the%20US%20installed%20in%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20era%20in%20the%20carpet%20capital%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EQcells'%20arrival%20in%20Dalton%20marked%20a%20new%20era%20in%20Whitfield%20County%2C%20which%20was%20devastated%20by%20the%20Great%20Recession.%20The%20housing-bubble%20burst%2C%20rippled%20through%20the%20carpet%20industry%2C%20and%20cost%20the%20county%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dailycitizen.news%2Fnews%2Flocal_news%2Fcarbondale-business-park-has-attracted-jobs-and-investment%2Farticle_3d4025a4-c81a-11ed-830d-e7ae46616883.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2010%2C000%20jobs.%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20peaked%20at%20about%2014%25%20in%20early%202009%20and%20the%20county's%20population%2C%20which%20had%20steadily%20grown%20for%20decades%2C%20plateaued.%20New%20housing%20construction%20halted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarl%20Campbell%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Dalton-Whitfield%20County%20Joint%20Development%20Authority%2C%20said%20that%20while%20carpet%20makers%20like%20Shaw%20Industries%20and%20Mohawk%20Industries%20survived%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FSMU13191403231400001%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20industry%20never%20returned%20to%20prerecession%20employment%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20consolidation%20and%20automation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decline%20led%20economic-development%20officials%20to%20try%20to%20diversify%20businesses%20in%20the%20area.%20Campbell%20said%20the%20local%20workforce%20already%20valued%20manufacturing%20because%20of%20the%20community's%20long%20history%20in%20carpet.%20This%20%E2%80%94%20combined%20with%20Dalton's%20proximity%20to%20Interstate%2075%2C%20a%20freight-rail%20depot%2C%20and%20a%20generous%2010-year%20property-tax%20abatement%20%E2%80%94%20helped%20close%20the%20deal%20with%20Qcells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Qcells%20opened%20its%20doors%20in%202019%2C%20Whitfield%20County's%20population%20has%20slowly%20started%20increasing%2C%20but%20not%20nearly%20as%20fast%20as%20Georgia's%20overall%20population%2C%20which%20grew%20by%201.7%25%20between%202020%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJevin%20Jensen%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Whitfield%20County%20Board%20of%20Commissioners%2C%20said%20part%20of%20the%20problem%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20housing.%20Each%20day%2C%20Jensen%20said%2C%2030%2C000%20people%20come%20to%20the%20county%20for%20work%20and%20then%20leave%20to%20go%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSurely%20some%20of%20those%20people%20want%20to%20live%20here%20but%20can't%20find%20a%20place%20they%20like%20or%20a%20place%20that's%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20Jensen%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20had%20any%20new%20apartments%20in%2020%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Local%20residents%20stand%20outside%20Dalton%20Station%2C%20a%20new%20apartment%20complex%20in%20Dalton%2C%20Georgia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f096e06080194819ff1b54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222841%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDalton%20Station%20is%20among%20the%20new%20apartment%20complexes%20opening%20in%20the%20city%20in%202024.%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Boudreau%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20lot%20can%20change%20in%20a%20year.%20Jensen%20said%20Dalton%20would%20have%201%2C200%20new%20apartments%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024.%20In%20early%20February%2C%20he%20attended%20a%20ribbon-cutting%20ceremony%20at%20a%20chic%20new%20studio-apartment%20complex%20that's%20close%20to%20downtown%20and%20designed%20to%20appeal%20to%20young%20professionals.%20Amenities%20include%20a%20gym%2C%20a%20common%20area%20with%20a%20pool%20table%2C%20and%20cornhole%20on%20the%20patio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfterward%2C%20Jensen%20gave%20BI%20a%20driving%20tour%20of%20three%20other%20developments%20around%20Dalton%2C%20including%20a%20multifamily%20apartment%20complex%20at%20an%20old%20jail%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20younger%20generation%20doesn't%20want%20to%20spend%20time%20on%20a%20remodel%2C%26quot%3B%20Jensen%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20move-in-ready%2C%20mixed-use%2C%20with%20retail%20and%20restaurants%20in%20one%20area.%20We%20had%20nothing%20like%20that%20for%20young%20professionals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowey%2C%20the%20Qcells%20employee%2C%20lives%20about%2030%20minutes%20outside%20the%20city%2C%20in%20Calhoun.%20He's%20noticed%20the%20new%20housing%20popping%20up%20in%20the%20area%2C%20along%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-i