ull%20of%20Lies%2C%20Half-Truths%20and%20Really%20Bad%20Drafting%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20underlined%20inconsistencies%20in%20the%20treatment%20of%20persecuted%20religious%20minorities%20from%20various%20countries%2C%20specifically%20highlighting%20the%20exclusion%20of%20persecuted%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20Sri%20Lankan%20Eelam%20Tamils.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20further%20emphasised%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20Assam%20Accord%20of%201985%2C%20which%20required%20the%20expulsion%20of%20foreigners%20who%20came%20to%20Assam%20after%20March%2025%2C%201971%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Sentinel%20%3C%2Fem%3Esaid%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20opposition%20leader%20%E2%80%9Cargued%20that%20providing%20citizenship%20to%20illegal%20who%20are%20non-Muslims%20contradicts%20the%20Accord%20and%20weakens%20the%20socio-economic%20fabric%20of%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20another%20petition%20at%20the%20SC%2C%20the%20All%20Assam%20Students%20Union%20(AASU)%20which%20had%20spearheaded%20the%20anti-foreigner%20agitation%20in%20Assam%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Flegitimizing-illegal-migration-all-assam-students-union-moves-supreme-court-challenging-citizenship-amendment-rules-2024-252044%5C%22%3Estated%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20court%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cthe%20notification%20of%20the%20Rules%20on%2011.3.2024%20stands%20in%20stark%20contradiction%20to%20the%20Assam%20Accord%20and%20Section%206A%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%201955.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAASU%20argues%20that%20these%20rules%20legitimise%20illegal%20migrants%2C%20adversely%20impacting%20indigenous%20culture%20and%20violating%20constitutional%20provisions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20is%20yet%20to%20set%20a%20date