vided%20all%20details%20of%20the%20bonds%20purchased%20by%20corporates%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20for%20public%20disclosure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwala%E2%80%99s%20seven-page%20letter%20written%20on%20March%2011%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Felectoral-bonds-case-bar-council-chief-calls-corporates-vulnerable-for-victimization-requests-prez-murmu-to-intervene-2933346%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CRevealing%20the%20names%20of%20corporates%20that%20had%20contributed%20to%20different%20political%20parties%20would%20render%20the%20corporates%20vulnerable%20for%20victimisation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20possibility%20of%20them%20being%20singled%20out%20by%20those%20parties%20that%20had%20received%20less%20contribution%20from%20them%2C%20and%20harassed%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20if%20the%20names%20of%20corporates%20and%20their%20quantum%20of%20contributions%20to%20various%20parties%20are%20revealed.%20This%20will%20be%20reneging%20on%20the%20promise%20given%20to%20them%20while%20accepting%20their%20voluntary%20contributions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20plea%20to%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20House%20to%20intervene%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20was%20to%20invoke%20Article%20143%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20empowers%20the%20President%20to%20consult%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%2C%20typed%20on%20the%20SCBA%20letterhead%2C%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Felectoral-bonds-case-bar-council-chief-calls-corporates-vulnerable-for-victimization-requests-prez-murmu-to-intervene-2933346%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20shatter%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20reputation%20the%20nation%20enjoys%20in%20the%20international%20arena%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2012%2C%20the%20SCBA%20executive%20committee%2C%20through%20a%20resolution%2C%20condemned%20the%20move%20and%20called%20it%20an%20attempt%20to%20undermine%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20authority.%20SCBA%20honorary%20secretary%20Rohit%20Pandey%2C%20in%20a%20written%20resolution%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20said%20the%20letter%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20written%20by%20Aggarwala%20in%20his%20capacity%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Association.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20noticed%20that%20below%20his%20signature%20on%20that%20letter%20he%20has%20inter%20alia%20mentioned%20his%20designation%20as%20president%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20has%20become%20expedient%20for%20the%20executive%20committee%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20to%20make%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20the%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20have%20neither%20authorised%20the%20president%20to%20write%20any%20such%20letter%20nor%20do%20they%20subscribe%20to%20his%20views%20as%20expressed%20therein.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20committee%E2%80%99s%20statement%2C%20issued%20on%20March%2012%2C%20underlined%20that%20the%20content%20of%20Aggarwala%E2%80%99s%20letter%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20attempt%20to%20overreach%20and%20undermine%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20and%20they%20%E2%80%9Cunequivocally%20condemn%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwala%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20post%20in%20May%202023.%20Though%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20President%20was%20to%20hold%20back%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20on%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20in%20December%202023%2C%20he%20was%20in%20the%20news%20for%20expressing%20%E2%80%9Cutter%20shock%E2%80%9D%20at%20former%20SCBA%20president%20and%20noted%20lawyer%20Dushyant%20Dave%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Ftop-lawyer-dushyant-dave-writes-open-letter-to-cji-over-listing-of-cases-in-sc-9057609%2F%5C%22%3Eopen%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%