%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365.jpeg%201242w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365-300x296.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365-500x494.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365-768x758.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365-96x96.jpeg%2096w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam2-min-1709639365-150x148.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-343950%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221226%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPoonam%20has%20trained%20over%203%2C000%20women%20in%20flower%20recycling.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20that%20the%20first%20step%20was%20sorted%2C%20the%20next%20step%20was%20selling%20it.%20But%20where%20would%20she%20sell%20it%3F%20She%20decided%20to%20set%20up%20a%20stall%20at%20Dilli%20Haat%20and%20at%20other%20exhibitions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20response%20was%20really%20good%20at%20the%20first%20stall%20I%20set%20up%20at%20Dilli%20Haat.%20Some%20teachers%20visited%20one%20of%20the%20exhibitions%20and%20wished%20to%20see%20my%20factory.%20Post%20that%2C%20they%20invited%20me%20to%20speak%20to%20their%20students%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Poonam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20things%20started%20looking%20up%2C%20she%20was%20hit%20by%20another%20roadblock%20%E2%80%93%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20With%20the%20entire%20country%20shut%2C%20there%20were%20no%20exhibitions%20too.%20Poonam%20decided%20to%20turn%20this%20into%20an%20opportunity.%20She%20started%20selling%20her%20products%20online%20through%20her%20website%2C%20Whatsapp%20and%20Facebook.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20one%20door%20shuts%2C%20another%20one%20opens.%20Along%20with%20creating%20an%20online%20presence%2C%20I%20also%20worked%20on%20building%20a%20space%20through%20which%20I%20deliver%20talks%20and%20conduct%20skill-based%20programmes%20to%20generate%20a%20livelihood%20for%20underprivileged%20women.%20It%20is%20called%20the%20Save%20Prithvi%20Foundation%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoonam%20is%20now%20a%20master%20trainer%20at%20Khadi%20India%2C%20National%20Cooperative%20Union%20of%20India%2C%20and%20has%20conducted%20training%20programmes%20with%20many%20government%20organisations%20like%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendras%20in%20Jammu%2C%20the%20rural%20development%20programme%20and%20more.%20She%20has%20trained%20over%203%2C000%20women%20and%20showed%20them%20a%20way%20to%20become%20self-reliant%2C%20while%20helping%20the%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20collects%20floral%20waste%20from%20over%2015%20temples%20in%20Delhi-NCR%20today%20and%20gets%20almost%20100%20kg%20of%20waste%20every%20three%20days.%20Besides%20dhoop%2C%20which%20is%20her%20bestseller%2C%20she%20makes%20idols%20and%20air%20fresheners.%20Her%20products%20range%20from%20Rs%2050-350%2C%20earning%20her%20a%20monthly%20income%20of%20Rs%202%20lakh.%20Her%20dhoop%20stand%20and%20packaging%20too%2C%20is%20made%20from%20waste.%20She%20employs%205%20women%20at%20her%20unit%2C%20who%20she%20calls%20the%20%E2%80%98flower%20recyclers%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Poonam%2C%20this%20business%20helped%20her%20build%20her%20identity%20and%20make%20a%20difference%20in%20the%20environment%20and%20lives%20of%20countless%20women.%20Her%20dream%20is%20to%20make%20India%20a%20country%20where%20not%20even%20one%20religious%20place%20throws%20flowers%20in%20the%20garbage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20all%20women%20like%20her%2C%20looking%20to%20fulfil%20their%20dream%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20get%20one%20opportunity%20in%20life%20to%20carve%20a%20path%20for%20ourselves.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20miss%20it.%20Live%20for%20yourself%20and%20do%20what%20makes%20you%20happy.%20The%20first%20step%20is%20always%20difficult%2C%20but%20once%20you%E2%80%99ve%20taken%20it%2C%20there%20is%20no%20looking%20back%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAaruhi%20Enterprise%20products%20will%20soon%20be%20available%20on%20Amazon%20and%20Flipkart.%20You%20can%20also%20purchase%20them%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.saveprithvi.com%2Fcategory%2Forganic-dhoop%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3B%20All%20photos%20courtesy%20Poonam%20Singh)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709706273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fpoonam5-1709639330.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D343922%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Poonam%20Singh%20started%20Aaruhi%20Enterprises%20to%20recycle%20floral%20waste%20from%20temples%20into%20incense%20sticks%20and%20more.%20She%20recycles%201%2C000%20kg%20waste%20per%20month%20and%20has%20upskilled%20over%203%2C000%20women%20so%20far%20with%20her%20awareness%20workshops.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F343922%2Ftemple-flower-waste-recycling-startup-homemaker-turned-entrepreneur-incense-sticks-gurugram-poonam-singh%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gas%20Industry%20Loses%20Bid%20To%20Block%20Green%20Building%20Codes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Gas%20companies%20and%20furnace%20manufacturers%20have%20one%20more%20chance%20to%20make%20their%20case%2C%20but%20it's%20an%20uphill%20battle.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709669675000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.huffingtonpost.com%2Fasset%2F65e7574c22000055004b781f.jpeg%3Fops%3D1200_630%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%2